  "De'Von Achane": {
    "summary": "As an effective one-man-army in South Beach, De'Von Achane projects to tally significant stats despite a bad Dolphins offense that will see its fair share of garbage time opportunities. Projecting 16% of Miami's total air yards in 2026, Achane's prevalence in the receiving game remains a key differentiator. Even at a slightly lower rushing and receiving profile than 2025 reflecting Miami's low win total expectation, Achane profiles as a bell-cow RB1 you can trust on draft day.",
    "pros": [
      "Very limited backfield competition with a strong profile for continued receiving work out of the backfield",
      "Significant offseason contract extension signals Miami's long-term commitment as the clear lead back",
      "Ranked #1 among all 55 qualified RBs in PFF rushing grade (91.0) in 2025 — elite efficiency that transcends situation"
    ],
    "cons": [
      "Miami projects for just 4.5 wins — tied for the lowest in the league — limiting touchdown upside and overall volume",
      "Malik Willis' ability to scramble could eat into Achane's short-area receiving work near the goal line",
      "League-leading 5.7 YPC in 2025 may be due for regression as defenses stack the box with Hill and Waddle no longer keeping them honest"
    ],
    "published": false
  },
